1. Sparse Index

A sparse index only includes documents that contain the indexed field, which can save space and improve performance when querying on fields that may not exist in every document.


db.users.insertMany([
  { name: "Alice", email: "alice@example.com" },
  { name: "Bob" },
  { name: "Charlie", email: "charlie@example.com" }
])

db.users.createIndex({ email: 1 }, { sparse: true })
